            configurations.runtimeClasspath.collect { it.isDirectory() ? it : zipTree(it) }
        }
    }

to my build.gradle fixed the issue, this I believe packs the classpath into the jar file, so at runtime it can actually find it, correct me if I&#39;m wrong though.
But this did seem to fix the problem for me

